1
00:00:01,668 --> 00:00:03,334
           [hissing]
                                 Mm hm.

2
00:00:03,404 --> 00:00:05,237
    [hiss]
                   Mm hm.

3
00:00:05,339 --> 00:00:06,173
                        Oh!

4
00:00:06,874 --> 00:00:10,608
    Antoine believes what
    he eats is<i> his</i> business.

5
00:00:10,711 --> 00:00:12,778
      Do other predators
      feel that way, too?

6
00:00:12,879 --> 00:00:13,956
     [agreeing]

7
00:00:14,081 --> 00:00:16,315
    Would any prey
    like to respond?

8
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:22,587
 Muriel? Does it bother you
 when Antoine tries to eat you?

9
00:00:24,058 --> 00:00:25,791
      Just because you're
       on opposite ends

10
00:00:25,893 --> 00:00:27,893
   of the food chain doesn't
   mean you can't work toge--

11
00:00:27,995 --> 00:00:28,729
        [elephant honks]

12
00:00:30,231 --> 00:00:32,297
  It doesn't mean you can't--

13
00:00:32,499 --> 00:00:33,065
            [boink]

14
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:34,333
         [angry growl]

15
00:00:34,435 --> 00:00:35,601
             Ahem!

16
00:00:35,803 --> 00:00:38,403
      It doesn't mean you
      can't work togeth--

17
00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:41,273
        [snarling growl]

18
00:00:41,375 --> 00:00:45,510
   Oh! I'm sorry, but the
  more you distract everyone,

19
00:00:45,612 --> 00:00:47,112
   the longer this will take.

20
00:00:47,214 --> 00:00:48,480
          [chittering]

21
00:00:48,682 --> 00:00:52,084
 I AM listening to you, but if
 you really want to be heard,

22
00:00:52,186 --> 00:00:54,319
  you should join our
  Predator-Prey-Support Group.

23
00:00:54,521 --> 00:00:56,689
      Then you could talk
       to everyone here.

24
00:00:57,291 --> 00:00:59,325
      You could teach all
     these hungry predators

25
00:00:59,427 --> 00:01:02,027
      the delights of a
     carrot-based cuisine.

26
00:01:03,697 --> 00:01:04,730
        Sorry, everyone.

27
00:01:04,832 --> 00:01:08,133
   I think <i>somebunny</i> just
   wants a little attention.

28
00:01:08,635 --> 00:01:11,470
       Now, since we all
       need to get along,

29
00:01:11,572 --> 00:01:14,606
 what if all Predators promised
 to only eat vegetables

30
00:01:14,708 --> 00:01:16,341
        while staying at
        the Sanctuary?

31
00:01:21,182 --> 00:01:23,949
                  Oh, Sandra.
                  You can do it!

32
00:01:24,351 --> 00:01:25,584
            [growl]

33
00:01:25,786 --> 00:01:26,885
            [whine]

34
00:01:29,156 --> 00:01:30,188
            [growl]

35
00:01:30,290 --> 00:01:31,189
               ♪♪

36
00:01:31,291 --> 00:01:33,658
     [gasp] Angel! Sandra! Wait!

37
00:01:33,860 --> 00:01:38,063
           [barking]

38
00:01:38,165 --> 00:01:41,032
         [angry growl]

39
00:01:41,134 --> 00:01:42,433
            [crash]

40
00:01:44,305 --> 00:01:48,373
 Hm. It might look like chaos,
 but Fluttershy makes it work,

41
00:01:48,475 --> 00:01:50,910
even <i>with</i> Angel running around.

42
00:01:51,912 --> 00:01:55,514
   <i> Oooh. Perhaps I can help</i>
   <i> those two get along,</i>

43
00:01:55,616 --> 00:01:58,984
    <i> before something here</i>
    <i> can go terribly wrong.</i>

44
00:02:38,059 --> 00:02:41,625
               ♪♪

45
00:02:41,796 --> 00:02:44,730
 Zecora found this little guy
 and brought him to my office,

46
00:02:44,832 --> 00:02:47,499
   but I thought he might do
   better at the sanctuary.

47
00:02:47,601 --> 00:02:50,068
               ♪♪

48
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:51,604
             [poof]

49
00:02:51,906 --> 00:02:54,807
<i>Bringing him here seemed</i>
<i>the right thing to do.</i>

50
00:02:54,909 --> 00:02:58,777
<i>I've never seen geckos breathe</i>
<i>smoke, though, have you?</i>

51
00:02:58,979 --> 00:03:01,280
    Oh! I certainly haven't!

52
00:03:01,682 --> 00:03:03,782
I thought we could take
a look at his diet,

53
00:03:03,884 --> 00:03:05,184
plus it's about
time for me

54
00:03:05,286 --> 00:03:07,385
to give all the animals
here a check up.

55
00:03:08,155 --> 00:03:10,155
    That's a wonderful idea.

56
00:03:15,896 --> 00:03:18,330
     If we really want to
     know what's going on,

57
00:03:18,432 --> 00:03:21,233
    we need to make sure the
    problem isn't your food.

58
00:03:25,573 --> 00:03:27,039
   I wouldn't worry too much.

59
00:03:27,141 --> 00:03:29,408
  It's probably just
  something he's been eating.

60
00:03:29,510 --> 00:03:33,713
   Oh, um! Is there anything
    else we can do for you?

61
00:03:34,115 --> 00:03:37,316
       <i> Ahh! Seeing what</i>
        <i> you two do,</i>

62
00:03:37,418 --> 00:03:40,852
     <i> the real question</i>
     <i> is: "Can I help YOU?"</i>

63
00:03:43,157 --> 00:03:45,691
   You mean... me and Angel?

64
00:03:45,793 --> 00:03:46,892
             <i>Mm hm.</i>

65
00:03:47,394 --> 00:03:50,295
         Oh, he's fine!
         We're fine... I-

66
00:03:50,397 --> 00:03:53,132
    I just don't always have
    time to indulge him.

67
00:03:53,634 --> 00:03:55,901
    But we're best friends.

68
00:03:56,403 --> 00:03:59,671
<i>Even the best of friends</i>
<i>need help from time to time.</i>

69
00:03:59,773 --> 00:04:03,343
<i>Come visit me in my hut,</i>
<i>should you change your mind.</i>

70
00:04:04,245 --> 00:04:07,246
     OK, thanks! But Angel
      and I are great!

71
00:04:07,548 --> 00:04:09,448
                    Ah! Goodness,
                     Fluttershy!

72
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:12,484
Is this the list of
what you do every day!?

73
00:04:12,786 --> 00:04:15,454
      How do you find time
       for anything else?

74
00:04:15,556 --> 00:04:19,858
Between here and teaching at
the school, I'm not sure I do.

75
00:04:24,098 --> 00:04:26,731
     You're going to love
     it here, little gecko.

76
00:04:28,202 --> 00:04:30,535
What is it? Not
fluffy enough?

77
00:04:32,206 --> 00:04:33,772
         Oh, I'm sorry.

78
00:04:33,874 --> 00:04:36,841
 We need to see if your
  food is causing your issue.

79
00:04:40,347 --> 00:04:41,179
              Huh?!

80
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:45,684
               Mm. Not now, Angel.

81
00:04:47,154 --> 00:04:48,087
                [hiss]

82
00:04:48,189 --> 00:04:50,355
      They're snake treats
      made to look like

83
00:04:50,457 --> 00:04:52,457
    chocolate chip cookies!

84
00:04:52,659 --> 00:04:56,228
       [chewing and gulp]

85
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:57,763
They're vegan!

86
00:04:57,865 --> 00:04:59,698
Pinkie Pie made a
whole jar of them.

87
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:02,268
They're all yours
if you promise....

88
00:05:02,670 --> 00:05:05,804
No more trying to eat
Muriel the Baby Elephant.

89
00:05:05,928 --> 00:05:11,528
               ♪♪

90
00:05:12,112 --> 00:05:12,678
    Ah!

91
00:05:12,780 --> 00:05:13,745
[chitter]

92
00:05:13,847 --> 00:05:16,481
               No, Angel. I have
               too much to do.

93
00:05:19,286 --> 00:05:21,053
           [coughing]

94
00:05:21,155 --> 00:05:24,823
        Oh! Careful, girl. That neck
        is still pretty sore.

95
00:05:25,793 --> 00:05:27,959
     Don't forget to shift
      your weight, Scout.

96
00:05:30,163 --> 00:05:31,697
                  What does she want?

97
00:05:32,599 --> 00:05:35,667
  Her neck is feeling better,
  but a massage every day

98
00:05:35,769 --> 00:05:38,905
  for the next week wouldn't
 hurt. I'll add it to my list.

99
00:05:39,907 --> 00:05:43,642
 Heh. Fluttershy, I've said it
 before, but I'll say it again.

100
00:05:43,744 --> 00:05:47,212
      This place would be
      a <i>zoo</i> without you!

101
00:05:47,314 --> 00:05:49,080
   [laughing with a chortle]

102
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:49,849
     [bonk]

103
00:05:50,751 --> 00:05:51,750
             Angel!?

104
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:55,387
   "Listen to you for once?"

105
00:05:55,489 --> 00:05:58,457
      Just WHAT exactly is
     that supposed to mean!?

106
00:06:00,928 --> 00:06:05,664
      Come back! I meant
      tell me, not... oh!

107
00:06:06,066 --> 00:06:07,366
           Well, whatever it is,

108
00:06:07,468 --> 00:06:09,701
           you're the only one
           he can tell about it.

109
00:06:09,803 --> 00:06:12,538
           Li'l fella just wants
           you all to himself.

110
00:06:12,740 --> 00:06:15,474
 Unfortunately,
that's not an option.

111
00:06:15,576 --> 00:06:18,609
      Aw, he's not causing
       any real trouble..

112
00:06:18,711 --> 00:06:20,077
[crash]
                         Ah!         
[birds squawk]

113
00:06:20,114 --> 00:06:21,546
   Other than that, possibly.

114
00:06:21,648 --> 00:06:22,514
  [crash]
  [elephant trumpets]

115
00:06:22,616 --> 00:06:24,583
       Or that. I'll just
         stop talking.

116
00:06:24,985 --> 00:06:27,886
    [groan] I'll take care of it.

117
00:06:31,025 --> 00:06:33,225
       I hope this is
       important, Angel.

118
00:06:33,327 --> 00:06:36,161
   I've barely made a dent in
   my to-do list for today.

119
00:06:37,145 --> 00:06:38,245
      [door opens]

120
00:06:38,369 --> 00:06:43,369
               ♪♪

121
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:45,605
         Concentrated
        Carrot Extract?

122
00:06:46,507 --> 00:06:49,174
      That's for reviving
   energy-sapped herbivores.

123
00:06:49,276 --> 00:06:50,842
    Are you feeling run down?

124
00:06:50,944 --> 00:06:52,244
                    [chittering]

125
00:06:52,346 --> 00:06:55,647
You just like the
 taste!? Ah! Angel!

126
00:06:55,749 --> 00:06:57,816
        That extract is
        in short supply!

127
00:06:57,918 --> 00:07:00,552
    What's gotten into you?
    Every day this week

128
00:07:00,654 --> 00:07:03,155
  you've been causing trouble
  when I have work to do!

129
00:07:05,026 --> 00:07:07,926
  <i>Of course</i> I know you
  can't talk to anypony else.

130
00:07:08,028 --> 00:07:11,996
    But that's not MY fault.
    I have responsibilities!

131
00:07:12,220 --> 00:07:13,020
           [growl]

132
00:07:16,537 --> 00:07:19,137
You're right. We
can't go on like this.

133
00:07:19,239 --> 00:07:21,940
I guess we do need to
see Zecora for help.

134
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:25,977
      <i> No need to sit</i>
      <i> and silently stew.</i>

135
00:07:26,179 --> 00:07:28,080
     <i> Tell each other</i>
     <i> what's bothering you.</i>

136
00:07:28,682 --> 00:07:32,951
  He's so impatient, even when
  he knows I have work to do.

137
00:07:34,655 --> 00:07:37,622
     Well, that's not true!
     We talk all the time.

138
00:07:38,859 --> 00:07:41,026
     Of course talking at
     the Sanctuary counts;

139
00:07:41,128 --> 00:07:43,695
  that's where I am when I
  don't have a class to teach.

140
00:07:44,865 --> 00:07:47,232
      What do you mean,
      that's the problem!?

141
00:07:48,902 --> 00:07:50,836
     You feel like I'm the
   only pony you can talk to

142
00:07:50,938 --> 00:07:52,637
  and all I do is ignore you.

143
00:07:52,739 --> 00:07:54,573
       Well, <i>I</i> feel like
        you don't care

144
00:07:54,675 --> 00:07:56,408
   about my responsibilities!

145
00:07:58,546 --> 00:08:03,215
   Heh.. Um, as you can see, we're
   kind of at an impasse.

146
00:08:03,717 --> 00:08:07,085
     <i> Ahh, such luck your</i>
     <i> coming here, indeed.</i>

147
00:08:07,187 --> 00:08:09,821
     <i> Behold, the antidote</i>
      <i> you need.</i>

148
00:08:10,123 --> 00:08:13,625
       Is... this what you
       meant by "help us"?

149
00:08:13,727 --> 00:08:16,228
      <i> When trouble brews</i>
      <i> between you two,</i>

150
00:08:16,330 --> 00:08:18,063
        <i> turning sister</i>
       <i> against brother.</i>

151
00:08:18,165 --> 00:08:20,766
      <i> True understanding</i>
      <i> is what's due,</i>

152
00:08:20,868 --> 00:08:23,002
       <i> each must come to</i>
       <i> know the other.</i>

153
00:08:23,904 --> 00:08:27,172
   <i> There's no time to</i>
   <i> waste, go directly home,</i>

154
00:08:27,274 --> 00:08:30,809
   <i> but you both must taste</i>
  <i> when you're finally alone.</i>

155
00:08:32,613 --> 00:08:34,813
               ♪♪

156
00:08:34,915 --> 00:08:36,515
        Not yet, Angel.

157
00:08:36,617 --> 00:08:39,551
   Zecora told us to take it
   together when we got home.

158
00:08:39,675 --> 00:08:44,075
               ♪♪

159
00:08:44,258 --> 00:08:47,259
  Oh! I suppose we could dust
  off the ol' picnic blanket.

160
00:08:47,361 --> 00:08:49,229
         It'll be just
        like old times.

161
00:08:50,231 --> 00:08:51,897
      We'll drink the
      potion and settle in

162
00:08:51,999 --> 00:08:53,799
     for a nice tea party.

163
00:08:53,901 --> 00:08:56,435
   I can barely remember
   the last time we did that!|

164
00:08:56,537 --> 00:08:58,971
       I've been so busy
       at the Sanctuary...

165
00:08:59,373 --> 00:09:02,207
  Though.. I really need to keep
  an eye on Zecora's gecko

166
00:09:02,309 --> 00:09:04,843
     and I haven't finished
     any of today's chores...

167
00:09:05,145 --> 00:09:08,013
 If I don't, the animals won't
  get the care they need!

168
00:09:08,115 --> 00:09:10,615
    Oh. Maybe we should save
    the potion until aft--

169
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:13,518
              Angel! Zecora said
              to go home first!

170
00:09:15,342 --> 00:09:16,042
         [burp]

171
00:09:18,125 --> 00:09:20,792
    I <i>know</i> she said we have
    to take it together so...

172
00:09:20,894 --> 00:09:22,360
   I guess I have to now.

173
00:09:24,507 --> 00:09:25,307
         [burp]

174
00:09:25,732 --> 00:09:29,135
     I wonder what it's
     going to dooWHOOOAA.-

175
00:09:30,337 --> 00:09:35,239
Whoa whoa whoa! Hang on, hold
up, am I a pony!? Why am I a pony!?

176
00:09:37,010 --> 00:09:38,276
            Eeeeek!

177
00:09:41,359 --> 00:09:43,859
               <i>♪ [dramatic sting] ♪</i>

178
00:09:44,184 --> 00:09:46,618
                Question: did we
                 switch bodies?

179
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:52,524
               ♪♪

180
00:09:53,326 --> 00:09:55,493
          Whoa! Whoa!

181
00:09:57,965 --> 00:10:01,032
                Seriously, I'm a
                pony? La la la la!

182
00:10:01,134 --> 00:10:02,301
             Talking is so cool!

183
00:10:02,403 --> 00:10:04,369
   Do you think this was what
   Zecora meant to happen?

184
00:10:06,373 --> 00:10:09,641
      How are you gonna do
      your <i>chores</i>!? Really?

185
00:10:09,743 --> 00:10:11,343
              <i>That's</i> what you're
              worried about?

186
00:10:13,614 --> 00:10:15,714
             Pff. Well, maybe I don't
             WANNA switch back!

187
00:10:15,816 --> 00:10:17,783
   I've only been able to
   talk to YOU since we met,

188
00:10:17,885 --> 00:10:20,285
       and now I can talk
       to anypony I want!

189
00:10:23,590 --> 00:10:24,956
Roses are red,
violets are blue,

190
00:10:25,058 --> 00:10:26,825
you sell flowers
and so do you!

191
00:10:27,227 --> 00:10:29,561
   Rubber baby buggy bumpers!
   Rubber baby buggy bumpers!

192
00:10:29,763 --> 00:10:30,495
          [baby cries]

193
00:10:30,597 --> 00:10:32,964
      Toy boat! Toy boat!
       Toy boa-AH!

194
00:10:33,667 --> 00:10:34,699
          Oh, come on!

195
00:10:36,603 --> 00:10:40,104
  I am so too listening! Quit
   bein' so bossy because -- Ah!

196
00:10:40,406 --> 00:10:41,239
            [sniff]

197
00:10:41,341 --> 00:10:42,341
 Are there carrots around here!?

198
00:10:46,447 --> 00:10:48,713
           You think Zecora gave
           us the wrong potion,

199
00:10:48,815 --> 00:10:50,649
           so you're gonna go to
           her hut in the forest

200
00:10:50,751 --> 00:10:52,251
               and get something
              to switch us back.

201
00:10:53,153 --> 00:10:54,153
                All by yourself?

202
00:10:54,255 --> 00:10:56,922
   You REALLY don't know what
    it's like being a bunny.

203
00:10:57,824 --> 00:11:00,692
  Good luck with <i>that</i>. I'm
  gonna go find those carrots.

204
00:11:00,994 --> 00:11:02,527
           [knocking]

205
00:11:02,629 --> 00:11:05,897
     "I need to finish your
      chores?" Ha, ha, ha!

206
00:11:06,099 --> 00:11:07,332
     I don't work for you!

207
00:11:07,434 --> 00:11:10,135
    And caring about other
    animals is a <i>you</i> thing.

208
00:11:10,436 --> 00:11:11,447
    <i> ♪ [horror sting] ♪</i>

209
00:11:11,572 --> 00:11:12,604
             [gasp]

210
00:11:12,706 --> 00:11:15,174
       The <i>stare</i>!? You
       can still do that?

211
00:11:15,376 --> 00:11:18,710
  Ugh! No fair making me do your
  bidding against my will!

212
00:11:18,812 --> 00:11:24,349
    <i> ♪ [horror film music] ♪</i>

213
00:11:24,451 --> 00:11:27,052
      All right! I'll go
      do your lame chores

214
00:11:27,154 --> 00:11:28,753
    while you go see Zecora.

215
00:11:32,739 --> 00:11:37,239
               ♪♪

216
00:11:37,364 --> 00:11:39,197
       Anypony know where
       that useless list

217
00:11:39,299 --> 00:11:41,467
   of Fluttershy's chores is?

218
00:11:42,269 --> 00:11:43,702
  Dr. Fauna: Hey, Fluttershy.

219
00:11:43,804 --> 00:11:46,037
    I was starting to wonder
    if you'd make it back.

220
00:11:46,239 --> 00:11:48,607
       Fluttershy! Oh,
      yeah! Uh, that's me!

221
00:11:48,709 --> 00:11:50,976
     Definitely Fluttershy,
     a hundred percent.

222
00:11:52,178 --> 00:11:52,711
                     [chirp]

223
00:11:52,813 --> 00:11:53,779
        Oh...kay.

224
00:11:53,881 --> 00:11:57,016
       See how.. <i>shy</i> I am?

225
00:11:58,018 --> 00:11:59,150
              I talk to animals...

226
00:11:59,252 --> 00:12:01,052
                I want to
                marry Discord...

227
00:12:01,154 --> 00:12:02,855
                Your list is
                over there.

228
00:12:03,657 --> 00:12:05,857
    Oh. Yeah. There's my
    good ol' list of chores

229
00:12:05,959 --> 00:12:07,793
     that I will absolutely
      NOT rush through

230
00:12:07,895 --> 00:12:10,829
  because I definitely do not
  have better things to do.

231
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:16,034
               Well, well, well.

232
00:12:16,236 --> 00:12:18,169
                    Remember <i>me</i>?

233
00:12:18,606 --> 00:12:22,207
  Ohh. I hope the gem tart stall
    is still there again.

234
00:12:22,409 --> 00:12:23,975
      I could use a snack.

235
00:12:24,177 --> 00:12:26,745
  You nearly bought every tart
   they had last time, Spike.

236
00:12:26,847 --> 00:12:28,313
      I can't imagine they
      wouldn't show up

237
00:12:28,415 --> 00:12:29,983
      when there's a great
       customer like you.

238
00:12:31,585 --> 00:12:33,752
Oh. Hi, Angel.
What's going on?

239
00:12:37,991 --> 00:12:39,459
Do you know what
he's trying to say?

240
00:12:39,783 --> 00:12:40,360
       Nope.

241
00:12:40,461 --> 00:12:43,194
Sorry, Angel. You should
probably find Fluttershy.

242
00:12:43,296 --> 00:12:45,330
If I see her, I'll let her
know you're looking for her.

243
00:12:45,432 --> 00:12:53,400
               ♪♪

244
00:12:53,524 --> 00:12:54,924
    [panting]

245
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:02,481
    [barking]

246
00:13:02,583 --> 00:13:04,849
           AND we're gonna keep
           at it until you start

247
00:13:04,951 --> 00:13:06,685
                   to develop a
                   taste for it.

248
00:13:09,322 --> 00:13:11,389
   Uh, check Muriel's trunk...

249
00:13:14,805 --> 00:13:15,405
[exhale]

250
00:13:15,506 --> 00:13:17,205
[sharp inhale]

251
00:13:17,330 --> 00:13:18,163
            [clunk]

252
00:13:18,965 --> 00:13:20,331
Ah, seems fine to me.

253
00:13:20,433 --> 00:13:22,000
As long as we don't
need those keys..

254
00:13:22,402 --> 00:13:23,068
             [small grunt]

255
00:13:23,170 --> 00:13:26,471
   Anyway. Let's see. Massage
    Clementine's neck...

256
00:13:26,573 --> 00:13:29,474
         [choking]

257
00:13:29,576 --> 00:13:30,475
         [thump thump]

258
00:13:31,077 --> 00:13:31,910
         [cough]

259
00:13:32,412 --> 00:13:34,279
   Get Scout to switch legs?

260
00:13:34,581 --> 00:13:36,047
           [snoring]

261
00:13:36,149 --> 00:13:37,683
Eh. Probably best not to wake him.

262
00:13:37,785 --> 00:13:39,784
    Did the thing with the
    thing, yada, yada, yada,

263
00:13:39,886 --> 00:13:40,986
   animals, animals, animals.

264
00:13:41,088 --> 00:13:45,256
  All that's left is.. monitor
 Zecora's gecko until bedtime!?

265
00:13:49,596 --> 00:13:52,330
     All right, dude. How
    about we do bedtime now?

266
00:13:54,201 --> 00:13:56,034
       Yeah, eating makes
         me tired too.

267
00:13:56,236 --> 00:13:59,037
   Which reminds me, there's
    some carrot extract

268
00:13:59,139 --> 00:14:00,672
      with my name on it.

269
00:14:01,975 --> 00:14:04,209
     OK! Let's get you fed
     and off to dreamland.

270
00:14:04,411 --> 00:14:05,543
    What do you eat, anyway?

271
00:14:07,414 --> 00:14:09,381
  Whaddya say, Snake? Can you
  find something else to eat

272
00:14:09,483 --> 00:14:11,316
   if I borrow those cookies
   for my friend here?

273
00:14:11,618 --> 00:14:14,953
               ♪♪

274
00:14:15,055 --> 00:14:17,156
           [gulping]

275
00:14:17,958 --> 00:14:18,657
             [burp]

276
00:14:19,759 --> 00:14:21,393
I'm sure
that's normal.

277
00:14:21,795 --> 00:14:23,395
There you go.
Problem solved.

278
00:14:23,597 --> 00:14:25,598
     I don't see what's so
     hard about this job.

279
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:29,400
Fluttershy is
SUCH a whiner!

280
00:14:29,502 --> 00:14:50,470
               ♪♪

281
00:14:50,623 --> 00:14:52,023
[knock]
             [squeak]

282
00:14:52,125 --> 00:14:53,491
               ♪♪

283
00:14:53,593 --> 00:14:55,126
    [squawk]

284
00:14:56,396 --> 00:14:57,195
         [slash sound]

285
00:14:57,697 --> 00:14:59,664
    [distant squawk]

286
00:14:59,766 --> 00:15:04,569
               ♪♪

287
00:15:04,671 --> 00:15:07,072
 <i> Quite a day, my fuzzy friend!</i>

288
00:15:07,174 --> 00:15:09,541
      <i> Did things work out</i>
      <i> for you in the end?</i>

289
00:15:12,045 --> 00:15:16,481
    <i> I'm sorry, dear bunny,</i>
  <i> that things seem so grave,</i>

290
00:15:16,583 --> 00:15:19,452
    <i> but I don't understand</i>
    <i> when you sign and wave.</i>

291
00:15:20,754 --> 00:15:25,621
<i>A single link to all the world.</i>
<i> only one in all the land.</i>

292
00:15:26,123 --> 00:15:30,157
 <i> How special she must be to</i>
 <i> you, the one who understands.</i>

293
00:15:31,259 --> 00:15:33,029
   <i> Perhaps if you explained</i>
    <i> what you wanted</i>

294
00:15:33,131 --> 00:15:34,899
  <i> to somepony who understood,</i>

295
00:15:35,001 --> 00:15:36,935
       <i> if you truly felt</i>
       <i> heard and valued,</i>

296
00:15:37,037 --> 00:15:39,005
   <i> all would return to good.</i>

297
00:15:40,207 --> 00:15:43,241
       <i> And if you were</i>
      <i> to both apologize,</i>

298
00:15:43,343 --> 00:15:45,076
        <i> having learned</i>
      <i> this little lesson,</i>

299
00:15:45,378 --> 00:15:47,479
        <i> I imagine that</i>
      <i> might bring an end</i>

300
00:15:47,581 --> 00:15:49,647
       <i> to the friendship</i>
       <i> therapy session.</i>

301
00:15:49,771 --> 00:15:54,171
               ♪♪

302
00:15:55,499 --> 00:15:57,999
    [grunting]

303
00:15:58,124 --> 00:15:58,990
        Dr. Fauna: Fluttershy?

304
00:15:59,092 --> 00:16:01,827
 Do you mind helping me look
 for Muriel the Baby Elephant?

305
00:16:02,329 --> 00:16:04,329
Oh, she's having
dinner with Antoine.

306
00:16:04,631 --> 00:16:06,364
             Antoine the PYTHON!?

307
00:16:06,666 --> 00:16:07,832
It was on the list:

308
00:16:07,934 --> 00:16:11,370
"Remember Antoine wants to
have Muriel over for dinner."

309
00:16:11,972 --> 00:16:16,608
 Not<i> over</i> for dinner! He
 wants to have her FOR DINNER!

310
00:16:17,110 --> 00:16:18,576
          Wait. WHAT!?

311
00:16:22,295 --> 00:16:26,595
               ♪♪

312
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:31,056
   Bad snake! Open your mouth
   this instant, Mister!

313
00:16:31,858 --> 00:16:36,127
           [barking]

314
00:16:36,229 --> 00:16:42,867
       <i> ♪ [tense music] ♪</i>

315
00:16:42,969 --> 00:16:43,801
            [scream]

316
00:16:44,971 --> 00:16:48,172
  What is going on!? You did
  all the chores on your list.

317
00:16:48,274 --> 00:16:49,274
        Huh!? Didn't you!?

318
00:16:49,776 --> 00:16:52,110
Well, technically,
I did'em, kind of.

319
00:16:52,212 --> 00:16:54,879
But more technically,
it's not <i>my</i> list.

320
00:16:55,181 --> 00:16:56,114
                 You wrote it!

321
00:16:56,216 --> 00:16:57,215
  Did I, though?

322
00:16:57,517 --> 00:16:59,618
    WHAT'S GOTTEN INTO YOU!?

323
00:17:00,220 --> 00:17:02,520
You do NOT wanna know.

324
00:17:05,926 --> 00:17:07,025
                        Huh?

325
00:17:10,330 --> 00:17:11,129
                    Angel?

326
00:17:11,231 --> 00:17:12,830
What's wrong
with her... him?

327
00:17:12,932 --> 00:17:13,833
What happened!?

328
00:17:14,735 --> 00:17:16,234
                 He's exhausted!

329
00:17:17,035 --> 00:17:17,913
      [soft whine]

330
00:17:18,038 --> 00:17:19,237
    Fluttershy, I need a jar

331
00:17:19,339 --> 00:17:21,740
      of concentrated
     carrot extract, STAT!

332
00:17:21,842 --> 00:17:24,175
Ah! It's locked in
the supply room.

333
00:17:24,477 --> 00:17:25,677
            Where are your keys!?

334
00:17:27,279 --> 00:17:28,379
              Uh....

335
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,783
    Any ideas how to get the
    keys out of the elephant

336
00:17:31,885 --> 00:17:33,318
    that's inside the snake?

337
00:17:34,020 --> 00:17:35,086
            [growls]

338
00:17:35,688 --> 00:17:39,090
     OK! Point taken. And
     I totally deserve it.

339
00:17:39,292 --> 00:17:41,760
 I did not provide you with the
  care that Fluttershy would.

340
00:17:42,362 --> 00:17:43,928
        But NOW you know
        what it's like

341
00:17:44,030 --> 00:17:45,330
        not to get the
       level of attention

342
00:17:45,432 --> 00:17:46,965
        to which you've
       become accustomed!

343
00:17:47,544 --> 00:17:48,644
        [soft growl]

344
00:17:49,369 --> 00:17:52,570
   The point is Fluttershy is
    trapped in my bunny body

345
00:17:52,672 --> 00:17:54,539
     and if we don't help
     her, maybe none of us

346
00:17:54,641 --> 00:17:57,642
will get her attention. I get
that you don't want to help <i>me</i>,

347
00:17:57,744 --> 00:17:59,544
but don't you want to help <i>her</i>?

348
00:18:03,483 --> 00:18:06,484
   <i> ♪ [military snare drum] ♪</i>

349
00:18:06,586 --> 00:18:14,354
               ♪♪

350
00:18:14,494 --> 00:18:15,760
       Here goes nothing.

351
00:18:16,162 --> 00:18:18,530
               ♪♪

352
00:18:18,654 --> 00:18:22,054
       [stretching]

353
00:18:22,178 --> 00:18:23,478
       [hissing]

354
00:18:23,637 --> 00:18:24,936
      [pop] [elephant trumpet]

355
00:18:25,438 --> 00:18:26,537
             [thud]

356
00:18:26,639 --> 00:18:27,339
             [gasp]

357
00:18:28,241 --> 00:18:30,441
    Now we just need to get
    those keys out of there..

358
00:18:30,843 --> 00:18:33,077
   [agressive hiss]

359
00:18:33,213 --> 00:18:34,546
   [trumpet blast]

360
00:18:35,548 --> 00:18:36,815
                  [clink]

361
00:18:37,117 --> 00:18:39,217
                    Ha, ha! Nice
                    one, snake.

362
00:18:40,353 --> 00:18:41,019
             [thud]

363
00:18:41,421 --> 00:18:42,854
 I guess Fluttershy was right.

364
00:18:43,156 --> 00:18:45,123
       Predators and prey
        <i>can</i> work together.

365
00:18:45,225 --> 00:18:50,761
               ♪♪

366
00:18:50,863 --> 00:18:52,831
            [grunt]

367
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:56,568
 This place is so. Much. Work!

368
00:18:57,070 --> 00:19:01,239
Oh! I know. I have no clue
how you do it all,

369
00:19:01,341 --> 00:19:02,740
but we are so grateful.

370
00:19:02,842 --> 00:19:08,313
♪♪

371
00:19:08,415 --> 00:19:11,349
            I can't believe she
            does this every day!

372
00:19:11,451 --> 00:19:14,052
             I just wish I could
             tell her myself..

373
00:19:14,154 --> 00:19:14,820
    What?

374
00:19:15,122 --> 00:19:20,025
    ♪♪

375
00:19:20,627 --> 00:19:21,526
            [whine]

376
00:19:22,028 --> 00:19:25,063
            ♪♪

377
00:19:25,165 --> 00:19:26,065
                 You're awake!

378
00:19:27,367 --> 00:19:29,300
    "It was so hard getting
     to Zecora's hut?

379
00:19:29,402 --> 00:19:30,535
  And impossible getting back?

380
00:19:30,637 --> 00:19:32,537
      You can't believe I
      survive like this?"

381
00:19:34,674 --> 00:19:37,208
    Well, I can't believe
    <i>you</i> work here every day!

382
00:19:37,310 --> 00:19:39,243
    These animals are crazy!

383
00:19:39,345 --> 00:19:41,347
      No wonder you don't
      have time for me!

384
00:19:42,849 --> 00:19:45,784
      My life is hard? No,
      YOUR life is hard!

385
00:19:46,286 --> 00:19:50,621
   You never appreciated me?
  No, I never appreciated <i>you</i>!

386
00:19:53,059 --> 00:19:56,294
  You're sorry? I'm sorry too!!

387
00:19:56,596 --> 00:20:00,530
  Come here, you little bunny
  who's a pony who's a bunny! Ooo!

388
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:02,700
             [zap]

389
00:20:06,906 --> 00:20:10,875
     Oh, my goodness! I'm
    back! I'm a pony again!

390
00:20:12,089 --> 00:20:12,689
    [clap]

391
00:20:14,514 --> 00:20:19,150
 Oh, Angel, I promise to always
 make time for you from now on.

392
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:25,424
 What do you mean maybe I won't
 have to? You want to do.. WHAT?

393
00:20:26,426 --> 00:20:27,992
 ...and that's when I realized

394
00:20:28,094 --> 00:20:30,595
   Fluttershy doesn't have to
   be the only one I talk to.

395
00:20:30,997 --> 00:20:33,466
      I can come here and
      talk to all of you.

396
00:20:34,868 --> 00:20:37,468
  And now that I know how much
   work goes into this place,

397
00:20:37,670 --> 00:20:41,072
 I suppose I could kinda, sorta
  help out every now and then.

398
00:20:45,512 --> 00:20:48,613
  Oh, Angel! That is so sweet,

399
00:20:48,715 --> 00:20:51,149
   but now that I know what
   you go through every day,

400
00:20:51,251 --> 00:20:54,419
   I understand why your time
    with me is so important.

401
00:20:54,621 --> 00:20:57,688
      I promise to always
      make time for you!

402
00:21:04,531 --> 00:21:07,065
  Turns out your friend, here,
 doesn't have a problem at all.

403
00:21:07,167 --> 00:21:10,100
      He isn't a gecko.
      He's a fire lizard!

404
00:21:10,202 --> 00:21:10,969
            [whoosh]

405
00:21:11,471 --> 00:21:13,638
           I forgot that before
           they get their flame,

406
00:21:13,740 --> 00:21:15,307
                it's hard to
                tell them apart.

407
00:21:16,309 --> 00:21:19,510
  <i> I'm glad to discover where</i>
  <i> the source of it lies,</i>

408
00:21:19,712 --> 00:21:23,915
 <i> or the fire that he breathes</i>
 <i> would be quite the surprise.</i>

409
00:21:24,017 --> 00:21:26,217
    Speaking of surprises...

410
00:21:26,619 --> 00:21:29,187
       Can you please
      <i>never</i> do that again?

411
00:21:29,311 --> 00:21:32,911
            ♪♪

